From a592f85473c22549357000b2989fbed8dc60baa1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: janet-darwin8-ppc <janet-darwin8-ppc@local>
Date: Sat, 16 May 2026 01:48:18 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 6/6] util.c: opt-out for Mach clock_get_time shim via
 JANET_NO_MACH_CLOCK_SHIM

The Mach-based clock_get_time fallback in janet_gettime() is gated
on "JANET_APPLE && !defined(MAC_OS_X_VERSION_10_12)" -- pre-10.12
Apple, identified by the absence of the 10.12 Availability marker.
That fires on Mac OS X 10.4 Tiger because the 10.4 SDK does not
ship MAC_OS_X_VERSION_10_12.

But macports-legacy-support (and other shim libraries used on
older macOS) provides a working clock_gettime() down to Tiger.
When linked against such a shim, the Mach fallback becomes dead
code that shadows a perfectly good libc function.

This patch adds an opt-out preprocessor flag.  When
JANET_NO_MACH_CLOCK_SHIM is defined, the #elif falls through to
the POSIX #else branch, which calls clock_gettime() directly
(resolved via the shim library).

No behavior change when JANET_NO_MACH_CLOCK_SHIM is not defined;
the existing Mach shim still runs by default.  Tiger builds
linking against macports-legacy-support can pass
-DJANET_NO_MACH_CLOCK_SHIM via CPPFLAGS (now plumbed through
both boot and final compile phases by the previous patch).
---
 src/core/util.c | 8 ++++++--
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/core/util.c b/src/core/util.c
index 66498384..82a0b96f 100644
--- a/src/core/util.c
+++ b/src/core/util.c
@@ -999,8 +999,12 @@ int janet_gettime(struct timespec *spec, enum JanetTimeSource source) {
     }
     return 0;
 }
-/* clock_gettime() wasn't available on Mac until 10.12. */
-#elif defined(JANET_APPLE) && !defined(MAC_OS_X_VERSION_10_12)
+/* clock_gettime() wasn't available on Mac until 10.12.  Define
+ * JANET_NO_MACH_CLOCK_SHIM to opt out of the Mach fallback and use
+ * clock_gettime() directly -- useful when linking against a shim
+ * library (e.g. macports-legacy-support) that provides
+ * clock_gettime() on earlier macOS. */
+#elif defined(JANET_APPLE) && !defined(MAC_OS_X_VERSION_10_12) && !defined(JANET_NO_MACH_CLOCK_SHIM)
 #include <mach/clock.h>
 #include <mach/mach.h>
 int janet_gettime(struct timespec *spec, enum JanetTimeSource source) {
